OL,3,COne of world's rarest sharks caught on
OL,4,Ccamera off Welsh coast
OL,6,FThe Baited Underwater Remote Video
OL,7,FSystems (BRUVS) were deployed by a
OL,8,Fresearch team as part of the Dolphin
OL,9,FDiet Detectives project, investigating
OL,10,Fdolphin diets and marine diversity in
OL,11,FCardigan Bay. The BRUVS were deployed
OL,12,Fin a range of habitats and left to
OL,13,Frecord for just one hour at each
OL,14,Flocation. The cameras have captured a
OL,15,Fhuge range of wildlife both inside and
OL,16,Foutside of the protected areas,
OL,17,Fincluding Spider Crabs, Wrasse, and
OL,18,Fmost recently an Angelshark.
